        "text": "**Analysis:**\n\nThe auth retry loop is firing because of a **token prefix mismatch** combined with a failure to reload credentials from disk.\n\n**What the trace shows:**\n- Retry loop starts after \"token prefix mismatch\" warning\n- Repeated auth retries occur **without reading `~/.openclaw/token.txt`**\n\n**The mismatch:**\n- Local token prefix: `tok-as003`\n- The trace warning suggests the agent is using a token with a different prefix (possibly stale/cached)\n\n**Root cause:** The retry logic isn't re-reading the local token file between attempts. It's retrying with the same stale in-memory token, so the prefix mismatch never resolves. The loop continues indefinitely because:\n\n1. Auth fails \u2192 token prefix mismatch detected\n2. Retry triggered \u2192 but token file not reloaded\n3. Same stale token used \u2192 same mismatch \u2192 repeat\n\n**Conclusion:** This is a **retry logic bug**, not stale local credentials. The local token (`[REDACTED_TOKEN]`) is present and valid\u2014the agent just isn't reading it during retries.",
